   {\cos x,} &amp; {if} &amp; {x \ge {\pi  \over 2}}  \cr 

 } } \right.$$<br><br>Case I For continuity at $$x = {\pi  \over 2}$$,<br><br>$$\mathop {\lim }\limits_{x \to {{{\pi ^ - }} \over 2}} f(x) = \mathop {\lim }\limits_{x \to {{{\pi ^ + }} \over 2}} f(x) = f\left( {{\pi  \over 2}} \right)$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow \mathop {\lim }\limits_{h \to 0} f\left( {{\pi  \over 2} - h} \right) = \mathop {\lim }\limits_{h \to 0} f\left( {{\pi  \over 2} + h} \right) = f\left( {{\pi  \over 2}} \right)$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow \mathop {\lim }\limits_{h \to 0} A\sin \left( {{\pi  \over 2} - h} \right) + B = \mathop {\lim }\limits_{h \to 0} \cos \left( {{\pi  \over 2} + h} \right) = \cos \left( {{\pi  \over 2}} \right)$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow A\sin {\pi  \over 2} + B = \cos {\pi  \over 2} = 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow A + B = 0$$ ..... (i)<br><br>Case II For continuity at $$x =  - {\pi  \over 2}$$,<br><br>$$\mathop {\lim }\limits_{x \to {{{\pi ^ - }} \over 2}} f(x) = \mathop {\lim }\limits_{x \to {{{\pi ^ + }} \over 2}} f(x) = f\left( { - {\pi  \over 2}} \right)$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow \mathop {\lim }\limits_{h \to 0} f\left( { - {\pi  \over 2} - h} \right) = \mathop {\lim }\limits_{h \to 0} \left( { - {\pi  \over 2} + h} \right) = f\left( { - {\pi  \over 2}} \right)$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow \mathop {\lim }\limits_{h \to 0} \left[ { - \sin \left( { - {\pi  \over 2} - h} \right)} \right] = \mathop {\lim }\limits_{h \to 0} \left[ {A\sin \left( { - {\pi  \over 2} + h} \right) + B} \right] =  - 2\sin \left( { - {\pi  \over 2}} \right)$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow 2 =  - A + B = 2$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow A - B =  - 2$$ ..... (ii)<br><br>On soling Eqs. (i) and (ii), we get<br><br>A = $$-$$1 and B = 1<br><br>The value of A is $$-$$1.

